Holi
events.description: Holi is hosted by OM, the organization for Indian spirituality and culture. Holi, also known as Dhuli Vandana in Sanskrit, is a Hindu holiday celebrating the triumph of true resolve and love, celebrated at the end of the winter season. This year, the actual holiday was on March 12th, but OM will be celebrating it during the Saturday of Carnival. It is celebrated annually by over one billion people worldwide, and a form of this celebration is throwing colored powder at each other, which OM will be doing. Holi during Carnival is an annual celebration at Carnegie Mellon and OM hopes to see you there!

events.description: Barbara Anderson teaches costume design and costume construction in The School of Drama. She has been instrumental in the creative development of generations of designers for the entertainment industry and is the co-author, with her husband Cletus, of the textbook Costume Design, published by Harcourt Brace. She has had a prolific design career, having designed costumes for film television, opera and theater.
